Would it make sense to also keep the old version? Because the current proof got a line longer, and the proof on line 523 also became more complicated...

It was lazy of me just to add a line to the proof of `range_traceForm_le_span_weight`: the new statement permits a much more direct proof. (I was just tying off loose ends before some travel and was short on time.)

I’ll have to come back to this when I return.

golf
```suggestion
  change _ = range (f.flip.dualMap.comp (Module.evalEquiv K V₂).toLinearMap)
  rw [← range_dualMap_eq_dualAnnihilator_ker, range_comp_of_range_eq_top _ (LinearEquiv.range _)]
  congr; ext; apply h
```
Thanks, I don’t have a laptop to test this but feel free to commit to this branch.

```suggestion
lemma dualAnnihilator_ker_eq_range_of_comm (f : V₂ →ₗ[K] Dual K V₂) (h : f.flip = f) :
```
is generally easier to prove things about (since `ext` can apply)
